      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-03-07T13:11:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This stuff still needs to go.  In general, we don\u0027t want to be downloading things inside of scripts running on the bots; those steps belong in the recipe, or we ensure that the dependencies get isolated or delivered via CIPD.  And we definitely don\u0027t want to be messing with git in these scripts; the bot code has already gotten us into the correct state, so doing more here can only hurt.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 48,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 62,
        "endChar": 26
      },
      "revId": "bae15ca960249ebbec7fcfb12974edf934b0ce46",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "744e2aa8_857c5ea7",
        "filename": "tools/skqp/make_universal_apk",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 62,
      "author": {
        "id": 5620
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-03-07T14:54:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Generally I would agree, but the motivation of this is to continuously test the build process and also test this script. IMO this is gives up high enough confidence that building the apk works. \n\nI think this simulates a desktop reasonably well in that we start out with a repo that is in a stable state and we go through the same motions as an individual would.\nWorst case scenario that line is a no-op. A failure would probably highlight a real problem.",
      "parentUuid": "3f77cfdb_b7990432",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 48,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 62,
        "endChar": 26
      },
      "revId": "bae15ca960249ebbec7fcfb12974edf934b0ce46",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "47483737_14abfe60",
        "filename": "tools/skqp/make_universal_apk",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 62,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-03-07T15:53:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Let\u0027s look at these individually.\nA. git clean -- either the generated files should be in .gitignore or in a directory outside the checkout. I don\u0027t see a problem with doing \"make clean\" or the equivalent.\nB. download_model -- IMO, this is not ideal, but probably not a huge concern. Eric might have a different opinion. Maybe we could make this a command-line option?\nC. remove_unneeded_assets -- I don\u0027t really understand this well enough to comment.\nD. setup_resources -- similar to above, if the dest is in .gitignore, I don\u0027t see a problem.\nE. git-sync-deps -- IMO, I don\u0027t think this is a good idea either in recipes or as a stand-alone tool. If I\u0027ve set up my third_party deps in a particular way or maybe applied a patch, I wouldn\u0027t want this tool to mess with it.",
      "parentUuid": "744e2aa8_857c5ea7",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 48,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 62,
        "endChar": 26
      },
      "revId": "bae15ca960249ebbec7fcfb12974edf934b0ce46",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7aa3b0f6_39c0e00e",
        "filename": "tools/skqp/make_universal_apk",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 62,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-03-07T16:20:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The worst case is probably that it puts the persistent checkout on the machine in an irrecoverable state and that machine fails all subsequent tasks.  We can\u0027t guarantee that those scripts don\u0027t download things to non-temporary locations on the bot, which may persist between tasks and cause subtle problems down the road. We have been burned enough times that I think it\u0027s a reasonable requirement to explicitly lay out all of the required inputs for each task, rather than have the task try to obtain them itself.  If it was feasible, I would support completely blocking network access by each task, after the sync step.  If this script is also intended to be run by humans, it\u0027s reasonable to require that the human has gotten their checkout into a sane state before running the script.\n\nAs for git-sync-deps, IMO it needs to disappear.  Maintaining checkouts is a subtle problem (as evidenced by the number of times we have been burned in the past), and it has an accepted solution, which is our supported workflow: gclient.  Gclient has many unit and integration tests and covers all of the subtle corner cases which have been found so far.  It has also been battle-tested in the field for almost a decade.  In comparison, git-sync-deps has NO tests, does not run on our bots, and plainly does not cover all of the cases that gclient does.  In my opinion, there is no reason for us to be in the business of writing our own gclient clone.  I fully support our developers doing things the way they want, but when they deviate from the supported workflow, we can\u0027t make any guarantees about what will happen.\n\nIf we (as an entire team) decided to change the supported workflow, then that would be fine.  Certainly, if we decided to stop using gclient in the supported workflow, we definitely need to stop pretending that we use it and change DEPS to something else.  And we would need to change all of our bots to use the new workflow, as we can only recommend a workflow if it is being tested.  IMO the above is not worth the gigantic maintenance headache just to solve a problem which already has a solution.",
      "parentUuid": "47483737_14abfe60",
